# Build artifacts
target/
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# IDE / editor noise
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# mdBook local build output. The deploy workflow publishes its own
# build to GitHub Pages; nobody should be committing this dir.
docs/book/

# Local scratch + dogfood output
*.local
*.dogfood
dogfood-output*.json

# Generated benchmark corpora; reproducible with `make -C benchmarks mirror`
# and full of synthetic secret-shaped fixtures.
benchmarks/corpora/
# Raw per-run RunResult JSONs are host-specific and regenerable with
# `make -C benchmarks bench`; the committed, human-facing rollups live in
# benchmarks/reports/ and the injected ../README.md tables.
benchmarks/results/

# Retired bench trees. The generators moved to benchmarks/generators/, the
# committed baselines to benchmarks/baselines/, and the scorer/differential
# logic to benchmarks/bench/. Only reproducible/generated leftovers (mirror
# corpus, ad-hoc result dumps) may still sit on disk here — never commit them.
tools/secretbench/
tools/diff_bench/

# Pre-existing local-noise paths
__pycache__/
.keyhog-cache.json
detectors/.keyhog-cache.json
# Stray ImageMagick render misdirected into a top-level path (12 MB .ps named
# "pathlib"); generated junk, never part of the source tree.
/pathlib

# Local coordination scratch — agent handoffs, dispatch notes, dogfood
# corpora paths. Never published to santhsecurity/keyhog. (STANDARD.md:
# prod-repo doc bleed rule.)
coordination/

# Bazel scaffolding — currently a PoC stub (every per-crate BUILD.bazel
# is comment-only, MODULE.bazel pinned to 0.5.7 while we're shipping
# 0.5.28). `bazel build //...` does not produce a working keyhog
# binary today; cargo is the real build system. Untracking until
# Bazel is fully wired and tested end-to-end, so we don't advertise a
# capability that doesn't exist.
.bazelrc
.bazelversion
BUILD.bazel
**/BUILD.bazel
MODULE.bazel
MODULE.bazel.lock
WORKSPACE
WORKSPACE.bazel
# Top-level scratch/audit/plan files that belong in the backup monorepo
# (santhsecurity/Santh) and `.audits/`, not in the standalone prod repo.
# NB: GAP_FINDINGS.toml is intentionally tracked (not ignored) — six contract
# tests across core/sources/scanner/cli read it as a source-of-truth registry,
# mirroring tests/FILE_GATE_MATRIX.toml, which was promoted out of this list for
# the same reason.
ROUNDS.md
TODO.md
TESTING_PROGRAM.md
KEYHOG_LINUX_QUALITY_PROGRAM.md
WAVE*_AGENT_PUSH.md
WAVE*.md
*_AUDIT*.md
*_AUDIT*.toml
FP_AUDIT_REPORT.md
*_PROGRAM.md
KIMI_AUDIT_*.md
CURSOR_AUDIT_*.md
CLAUDE_AUDIT_*.md
plan.md
PLAN.md
plans/
.audits/

# Runtime vyre JIT/PTX + pipeline caches written next to the binary during scans.
.cache/
NUL

# Per-host cross-device bench raw JSONs (regenerable via benchmarks/cross_device.sh).
# The committed, human-facing snapshot is benchmarks/reports/cross-device.md.
benchmarks/results-cross-device/
